 Here's a C++ function that takes a reference to a `std::string` containing markdown formatted text and returns a `std::string` containing html formatted text using the [markdown-it](https://github.com/markdown-it/markdown-it) library:
```cpp
#include <string>
#include <stdexcept>
#include <iostream>
#include <sstream>
#include <filesystem>
#include <markdown-it.h>

std::string markdown_to_html(const std::string &markdown_text) {
    if (markdown_text.empty()) {
        return "";
    }

    // Check if the file exists and is readable
    std::filesystem::path md_file(markdown_text);
    if (!std::filesystem::exists(md_file) || !std::filesystem::is_regular_file(md_file)) {
        throw std::runtime_error("Markdown file not found or not readable");
    }

    // Read the markdown file
    std::string file_content = std::string(std::ifstream(md_file).rdbuf());

    // Initialize markdown-it parser
    md_parser_t md_parser;
    md_parser_init(&md_parser);

    // Parse the markdown content
    char* parsed_content = md_parser_parse(&md_parser, file_content.c_str());

    // Convert parsed content to html
    std::stringstream html_content;
    html_content << md_parser_get_html(&md_parser);

    // Clean up memory
    free(parsed_content);
    md_parser_deinit(&md_parser);

    return html_content.str();
}

int main() {
    std::string markdown_text = "# Heading 1\n\nThis is the first paragraph.\n\n## Heading 2\n\nThis is the second paragraph.";
    std::string html_text = markdown_to_html(markdown_text);

    std::cout << "Markdown:\n" << markdown_text << std::endl;
    std::cout << "HTML:\n" << html_text << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```
This code snippet includes the markdown-it library and creates a `markdown_to_html` function that takes a `std::string` containing markdown formatted text as input and returns a `std::string` containing html formatted text. The function reads the markdown text from a file, parses it using the markdown-it library, and returns the html content.

Please note that you need to build the markdown-it library with C++11 support and link it to your project for this code to work. You can find the instructions on how to build markdown-it for C++ on the [official GitHub repository](https://github.com/markdown-it/markdown-it/blob/master/README.md#cpp).

